"57:2:10" : {s: 57, a: 2, w: 10, r: "شيا", t: "شَىْءٍۢ", l: "شَىْء", lc: 283, tl: "shayin", lb: "কিছু, বস্তু, কোনো কিছু",e: "things", b: "কিছুর", i: "sesuatu", f: 179, rm: "to will/wish. shaiun (pl. ashyaaun) - thing/matter, affair in any way, at all, what is willed or wished, aught, any extent. In direct objective case it is often used to denote the meaning a little, bit, at all. Adverbially it means in any way, at all."},
"57:2:11" : {s: 57, a: 2, w: 11, r: "قدر", t: "قَدِيرٌ", l: "قَدِير", lc: 45, tl: "qadīrun", lb: "মহাক্ষমতাবান, পরিপূর্ণ সক্ষম/ সর্বশক্তিমান (القَدِيْر)",e: "All-Powerful", b: "সর্বশক্তিমান", i: "berkuasa", f: 37, rm: "to measure/decree/determine/stint/straiten, to have power, to be able, a measure, means, ability, a term/decree, doom, destiny, measured, decreed."},
